Research Interests

Quantitative Finance

Development of mathematical models for derivatives pricing, risk management, and portfolio optimization using stochastic processes and numerical methods.

Machine Learning Applications

Application of deep learning and statistical methods to financial forecasting, algorithmic trading, and market microstructure analysis.

Computational Mathematics

Implementation of efficient numerical algorithms for solving partial differential equations in finance and engineering applications.

Philosophy

"Mathematics is the language with which God has written the universe. In quantitative finance, we decode this language to understand market dynamics and create value through rigorous analysis and computational innovation."

My approach combines theoretical rigor with practical implementation, believing that the most elegant solutions emerge from deep mathematical understanding paired with computational efficiency. I strive to bridge the gap between academic research and industry applications, creating tools that are both mathematically sound and practically useful.
